31/01/2006
ADANA, Turkey -- Four people were injured Monday (30 January) in a bomb explosion at a Turkish-American friendship association in Adana, southern Turkey. 
Adana is close to the Incirlik base, which is used by the US military for logistical support of operations in Iraq and Afghanistan. 
No group or organisation has claimed responsibility for the blast. 
(NTV, AP - 30/01/06)
